   "source": [
    "# 3. Preprocessing Pipeline"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## 3.1 Text Cleaning\n",
    "We combine the article title and description into a single string, then lowercase it, strip non-alphabetic characters, and collapse whitespace so the model sees clean input."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 6,
   "execution_count": 7,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [
    {
     "name": "stdout",
     "output_type": "stream",
     "text": [
      "Sample cleaned text:\n",
      "wall st bears claw back into the black reuters reuters shortsellers wall streets dwindlingband of ultracynics are seeing green again\n"
     ]
    }
   ],
   "source": [
    "# Combine title + description into one field for each article.\n",
    "train_df['full_text'] = train_df['title'].astype(str) + ' ' + train_df['description'].astype(str)\n",
    "test_df['full_text'] = test_df['title'].astype(str) + ' ' + test_df['description'].astype(str)\n",
    "\n",
    "# Import and apply the cleaning function from src/preprocessing\n",
    "from src.preprocessing import clean_text\n",
    "train_clean = train_df[\"full_text\"].apply(clean_text)\n",
    "test_clean = test_df[\"full_text\"].apply(clean_text)\n",
    "\n",
    "print(\"Sample cleaned text:\")\n",
    "print(train_clean.iloc[0][:200])\n"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## 3.2 Tokenization & Vocabulary Building\n",
    "We fit a Keras Tokenizer **only on training data** to prevent leakage. The vocabulary is capped at 20,000 words and an `<OOV>` token handles unseen words at inference time. The fitted tokenizer is saved to `models/tokenizer.pickle` for reuse."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 7,
   "execution_count": 8,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [
    {
     "name": "stdout",
     "output_type": "stream",
     "text": [
      "Tokenizer saved. Vocabulary size: 91344\n"
     ]
    }
   ],
   "source": [
    "# Fit the tokenizer ONLY on training data to prevent leakage.\n",
    "from src.preprocessing import build_tokenizer\n",
    "\n",
    "tokenizer = build_tokenizer(\n",
    "    train_clean,\n",
    "    max_words=20000,\n",
    "    save_path='models/tokenizer.pickle'\n",
    ")\n"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## 3.3 Sequence Padding\n",
    "Articles vary in length, so we pad every sequence to 128 tokens. We use **post-padding** (zeros at the end) so the LSTM reads the sentence start first."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 8,
   "execution_count": 9,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [
    {
     "name": "stdout",
     "output_type": "stream",
     "text": [
      "X_train shape: (120000, 128)\n",
      "X_test  shape: (7600, 128)\n"
     ]
    }
   ],
   "source": [
    "# Convert texts to integer sequences and pad/truncate to fixed length.\n",
    "from src.preprocessing import prepare_sequences\n",
    "\n",
    "MAX_LEN = 128\n",
    "X_train = prepare_sequences(train_clean, tokenizer, max_len=MAX_LEN)\n",
    "X_test = prepare_sequences(test_clean, tokenizer, max_len=MAX_LEN)\n",
    "\n",
    "print(f\"X_train shape: {X_train.shape}\")\n",
    "print(f\"X_test  shape: {X_test.shape}\")\n"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## 3.4 Label Preparation\n",
    "The raw AG News CSV stores labels as 1-based integers (`1` = World, `2` = Sports, `3` = Business, `4` = Sci/Tech). Keras expects 0-based one-hot vectors, so we subtract 1 and apply `to_categorical`."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 9,
   "execution_count": 10,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "# AG News uses 1-based labels (1-4). Subtract 1 and one-hot encode for Keras.\n",
    "from tensorflow.keras.utils import to_categorical\n",
    "\n",
    "y_train_oh = to_categorical(train_df['class_index'] - 1, num_classes=4)\n",
    "y_test_oh = to_categorical(test_df['class_index'] - 1, num_classes=4)\n"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## 3.5 Train/Validation Split\n",
    "We reserve 10 % of the training data as a validation set. The split is **stratified** so each news category appears in the same proportion as the full training set."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 10,
   "execution_count": 11,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [
    {
     "name": "stdout",
     "output_type": "stream",
     "text": [
      "Train      : (108000, 128)\n",
      "Validation : (12000, 128)\n",
      "Test       : (7600, 128)\n"
     ]
    }
   ],
   "source": [
    "# 3.5 Train/Validation Split\n",
    "# 90/10 stratified split keeps class proportions identical in both sets.\n",
    "from sklearn.model_selection import train_test_split\n",
    "\n",
    "X_tr, X_val, y_tr, y_val = train_test_split(\n",
    "    X_train, y_train_oh, test_size=0.1, random_state=42, stratify=y_train_oh\n",
    ")\n",
    "\n",
    "print(f\"Train      : {X_tr.shape}\")\n",
    "print(f\"Validation : {X_val.shape}\")\n",
    "print(f\"Test       : {X_test.shape}\")\n"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## 3.6 Saving Arrays\n",
    "We export the six final NumPy arrays (`X_train`, `y_train`, `X_val`, `y_val`, `X_test`, `y_test`) to `data/processed/` so teammates can load them directly without re-running preprocessing."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 11,
   "execution_count": 12,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [
    {
     "name": "stdout",
     "output_type": "stream",
     "text": [
      "Arrays saved to data/processed/\n",
      "  Train      : (108000, 128)\n",
      "  Validation : (12000, 128)\n",
      "  Test       : (7600, 128)\n",
      "  Vocab size : 91344\n"
     ]
    }
   ],
   "source": [
    "# Export the six final arrays so teammates can skip preprocessing.\n",
    "import os\n",
    "import numpy as np\n",
    "\n",
    "save_dir = 'data/processed'\n",
    "os.makedirs(save_dir, exist_ok=True)\n",
    "\n",
    "np.save(os.path.join(save_dir, 'X_train.npy'), X_tr)\n",
    "np.save(os.path.join(save_dir, 'y_train.npy'), y_tr)\n",
    "np.save(os.path.join(save_dir, 'X_val.npy'), X_val)\n",
    "np.save(os.path.join(save_dir, 'y_val.npy'), y_val)\n",
    "np.save(os.path.join(save_dir, 'X_test.npy'), X_test)\n",
    "np.save(os.path.join(save_dir, 'y_test.npy'), y_test_oh)\n",
    "\n",
    "print(f\"Arrays saved to {save_dir}/\")\n",
    "print(f\"  Train      : {X_tr.shape}\")\n",
    "print(f\"  Validation : {X_val.shape}\")\n",
    "print(f\"  Test       : {X_test.shape}\")\n",
    "print(f\"  Vocab size : {len(tokenizer.word_index)}\")\n"
   ]
  },
